At the same time, another member of the team steps forward, not knowing how vital she is to mankind's survival. Prepare for "Eclipso vs. Donna Troy" ‚Äì with an ending that will shock you!

FLASH FACT! Where is he? Or should we say when?

Kid Flash wakes up in the 31st century where the speed force doesn't exist, Brainiac has taken over earth, and his only ally is Patty Spivot, who has taken up the role of Hot Pursuit. It's up to the impromptue duo to fix the speed force, and get back to the 21st century before Kid Flash is erased from time itself.

description:
FLASH FACT! She is ready to reveal the Amazons' secret!¬†
¬†
Lois and Jimmy are on assignment in Paris covering a fashion show. Lois is talking with Perry asking for more serious work. ¬†Concurrently the Atlanteans are launching an attack on Paris which results in Jimmy disappearing while Lois recovers his camera and is rescued by Amazons. ¬†She is taken to London where she discovers she is to be retrained as a member of Amazon society. ¬†She also discovers that Jimmy's camera is in fact a communication device and she uses it to talk with Cyborg. ¬†She volunteers to fill Jimmy's position which was to collect information on the Amazons and make contact with the resistance. ¬†As she progresses through the re-education she learns about Amazons society. ¬†Just before being subjected to physical reconditioning (of which most people die) she escapes where she is partially rescued by a member of the resistance, but with Amazons on her tail she doesn't get far.

description: Three years have passed since the war with the orbiting stations, the city is devastated, many of its inhabitants are surviving in some way, many others are dying in some other way. A huge crater seems to bear witness-as bastions-the stupidity of war. The city had to impose new rules: to ensure compliance with the laws, law enforcement powers have been expanded enormously and a new police force was even created, the Proconsuls, who administer justice with an iron fist and keep the city in the grip of fear. In this scenario, Nathan, still sorely tried by the loss of so many people dear to him, will face yet another, painful mourning . That for Sara McBain.
name: Dopo l'Apocalisse

description: After the mysterious death of Sara Mc Bain, Nathan Never is contacted by Senator Sawyer, that wants the agent to be part of a team that will investigate the contradictions about that event. The Team, which operates under ¬† ¬†the "unofficial" direction of the senator, is also composed by ¬†Mark Greenberg, forensic, Vera Mills, computer expert and Wes Redding, head of the operational core. Since ¬†the beginning of the investigation it is clear that the senator's concerns are not entirely unfounded: in fact, someone is trying to kill the only witness of the event .

Classified!¬†¬†
¬†

Zee Hernandez has always been the soul of the city, and the one person who could keep Matty's ego in check ‚Äì most of the time. In her final solo issue of the series, we check back in with Zee, last seen in issue #59, and discover what secret she's been holding on to all this time.

description:
Hana Suzuki loves only two things in life: eating and sleeping. So when handsome classmate Izumi Oda asks Hana‚Äìhis major crush‚Äìto join the school hockey club, persuading her proves to be a difficult task. True, the Grand Hockey Club is full of boys‚Äìand all the boys are super-cute‚Äìbut given a choice, Hana prefers a sizzling steak to a hot date. Then Izumi mentions the field trips to fancy resorts. Now Hana can‚Äôt wait for the first away game, with its promise of delicious food and luxurious linens. Of course there‚Äôs also the getting up early, working hard, and playing well with others. How will Hana survive?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 2: Bravo, Ekiben

description: HERALD VS. HERALD FOR THE FATE OF ALL LIFE IN THE UNIVERSE! The High Evolutionary has stolen the power to replace Galactus, the lives of billions hang in the balance, and the one threatening to doom them all...is the Silver Surfer!? Marvel's most epic cosmic battle of the year is right here!

First, Wolverine was sent to hell. Then he was forced to fight for control of his own mind against demonic invaders. All thanks to the machinations of a mysterious group called the Red Right Hand. Who are they and what is their grudge against Logan? And how do they hope to survive now that Wolverine has come looking for some revenge of his own?

description: The Grand Hockey Club is already the most fabulous club in the school: That‚Äôs because the players are all super-hot guys (plus their sidekick Hana). But now the club is even more glam. Enter Yukio Francois de Saint-Martin, the club‚Äôs new faculty advisor. This tall, blond Frenchman is sexy, passionate...and totally out of his mind. Can the hockey club survive his crazy plans?

description:
Hana Suzuki has it good: she‚Äôs the only girl in the Grand Hockey Club, and all the other members are super-hot guys. But the dream may be over. If the Hockey Club doesn‚Äôt win its next match, the school will disband it! Hana and the boys are pretty much the worst hockey players ever. Can they get their act together in time to save the club?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 6: Encounter With the Unknown
  • Chapter 7: Judo Dreams!?

description:
Lieutenant Levka Kosilev was a man of principle, a man who would repay a debt of honour. The Russian officer had only survived the dark days of World War II thanks to the actions of a brave American corporal and his squad. He knew how much he owed them.
Some years later Levka ‚Äî now an observer with the forces of the North during the Korean War ‚Äî expectedly found himself in a position to settle the debt. To do so, however, he would have to defect. Could he do it?
name: The Defector? Which Side Is He On?

description:
Celebrating the 50th anniversary with this specially written story.
¬†
Dave, Brian, Pete and Sid were undoubtedly the worst soldiers their C.O. had ever come across. He doubted they would ever get through their basic training. But Sergeant Rod Black thought differently, he could see something in the four that no one else could.
And one night in June some 50 years ago he and his misfit squad got the chance to prove him right‚Ä¶or wrong!

description:
When Ned Dolan flicked a penny in the air and David Bradford called tails, it looked as though he had signed his own death warrant ‚Äî for the loser was to become bait for a deadly German sniper. And Dolan had never ‚Äî but never ‚Äî lost a toss with this special penny.
¬†
Originally Commando No. 368 and reprinted in Commando 1091.

description:
It was dead unlucky, that Stirling bomber. Flying low it would catch most of the flak, flying high it was certain to be pounced on by enemy fighters. Every time the crew set off on another mission they wondered if it was going to be their last. Even its number, five-three-five, added up to thirteen‚Ä¶
¬†
Originally Commando No 869 and reprinted in Commando No 2159.
